<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 5:11PM PDT  by NWS Reno</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Mono County
through 645 PM PDT...
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Benton, Chalfant, Benton Hot Springs, Glass Mountain and White
Mountain Peak.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
